Veil of Shadows</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=thetank01>TheTank01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 86<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/18/02 8:24:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1412.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   or...</span><hr size=1> Or perhaps you could have people ready to move on patch day like mine does. We aren't &quot;uber&quot;, but we managed to take out Zlandicar, Yelinak and Severilous all in 1 day. Heck, we've done even more than that after a patch day before.<br>
<br>
How? We have people ready to move, we have porters who don't whine and scream about having to pick up people from random places. They know their job for setting up a raid. For first broods? CoH is your friend! Non-kos mages speed things along. By the time people are arriving you should have your CoH group set up or the mage on the way to room. <br>
<br>
Is this wrong? I don't think so. It's not really our fault if a guild takes an hour to get to a place and we take 15 min. If you are really desperate for a mob that spawns after patch, set it up before hand for everyone to camp there and be ready to log in right after patch.<br>
<br>
Going to knock over Vindi after Severilous for the heck of it.. monk in SS, suddenly we're told Yelinak is up, but 3 other guilds had atleast 1 member in zone. We showed up with 30 within 10 min and they left.<br>
<br>
Sad as it is.. most problems for mid-level guilds getting mobs is they aren't fast.  Talk to your wizards and druids, explain to them they are a key part of getting the force there. Most times, it IS their fault (waits for screaming porter to flame in forum) because they don't speak up and say &quot;who needs to be picked up and from where?&quot;. Unless you have everyone willing to drop what they are doing for a big mob at a moment's notice, you are never going to get those mobs. They don't sit up and tell other guilds &quot;We're waiting for guild_01 to come kill us, please go away!&quot;.<br>
<br>
