I don't think this is the answer. This is the patented VI ragefire fix; whereby handing clerics their epics upon reaching level 54ish. Well, not exactly, but you get the message. I think reducing spawn timers on the most contested mobs will make guilds progress at a very accelerated rate, far moreso than they are now. This would, in effect, further help in trivializing older world content.<br>
<br>
If a timer was indeed adjusted to the most competitive mobs, King TOrmax will probably be #1 mob to be adjusted because he's currently the easiest mob for his loot table. Considering Tormax drop his head, used to make 110 mana FT-2 boots, getting more of these into the guild, esp to clerics at the lower end will help greatly to trivialize older-world content. <p><center><p><font size = 3 colo = "blue"><b>Wilhelmm D'Averam<br>Warlord of the Apocalypse</b></font></p></center>

